\pard\f0\fs28 Perennials. Stems terete. Leaves all basal. Inflorescence terminal, capitate, of 1-10 somewhat flattened, 1- to 4-flowered spikelets, subtended by 1 or 2 bracts with sheathing base and herbaceous lamina. Glumes distichous. Flowers hermaphrodite; perianth of 3-6 small bristles or absent. Stamens 3. Stigmas 3. Nut trigonous, without a persistent style-base.
\par

